STDF Rules

The Prudential Regulation Authority’s (PRA) Stress Testing Data Framework (STDF) that describes the requirements for submitting data to the PRA for the purposes of stress testing the capital positions of major UK banks.

Rule Id Rule Type Importance Description RejectOnFailure Field or Table
10005 Business Rule Error If ALM asset liability class = “Households assets”, then Scheduled payment should be populated. BOE Discretion [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][ALM asset liability class]
          [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][Scheduled payment]
10006 Business Rule Error If ALM product type = “Mortgage loans”, then Weighted average loan to value should be populated. BOE Discretion [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][ALM asset liability class]
          [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][Weighted average loan to value]
10007 Business Rule Error If ALM product type <> “Mortgage loans”, then Weighted average term should be populated. BOE Discretion [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][ALM asset liability class]
          [AssetLiabilityManagement][Fixed_rates][Weighted average term]
10124 Pattern Rule Warning The dimensions Balance sheet item market volume level 1, Balance sheet item market volume level 2, Balance sheet item market volume level 3 and Market volume product type are related to each other as populated in the template using the data validation drop downs i.e. the selection of one data item restricts what can be chosen for the other data items. This constraint should be maintained while populating the template. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Market_volumes_UK_only]
10125 Pattern Rule Warning The dimensions Profit or loss level 1 other expense and Profit or loss level 2 other expense are related to each other as populated in the template using the data validation drop downs i.e. the selection of one data item restricts what can be chosen for the other data item. This constraint should be maintained while populating the template. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Other_expense_details]
10126 Pattern Rule Warning The dimensions Profit or loss level 1 other income, Profit or loss level 2 other income, Asset Liability class retail other income and Other income product type are related to each other as populated in the template using the data validation drop downs i.e. the selection of one data item restricts what can be chosen for the other data items. This constraint should be maintained while populating the template. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Other_income_details]
10127 Pattern Rule Warning The dimensions Profit or loss business line level 1 and Profit or loss business line level 2 are related to each other as populated in the template using the data validation drop downs i.e. the selection of one data item restricts what can be chosen for the other data item. This constraint should be maintained while populating the template. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Profit_or_loss_business_line]
10128 Pattern Rule Warning The dimensions Profit or loss level 1 and Profit or loss level 2 are related to each other as populated in the template using the data validation drop downs i.e. the selection of one data item restricts what can be chosen for the other data item. This constraint should be maintained while populating the template. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Profit_or_loss_group_only]
10131 Unique Rule Error Each combination of the dimensions (Organisational unit level 1, Organisational unit level 2, Organisational unit level 3 (if applicable), Country of exposure, Profit or loss item level 1 cards other income, Profit or loss item level 2 cards other income, Asset liability class retail cards, Card product type, Projection period, and Scenario) should be uniquely populated in the template i.e. there should not be multiple rows of data for each unique combination of these data items. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Cards_other_income]
10132 Unique Rule Error Each combination of the dimensions (Balance sheet item market volume level 1, Balance sheet item market volume level 2, Balance sheet item market volume level 3, Market volume product type, Projection period, and Scenario) should be uniquely populated in the template i.e. there should not be multiple rows of data for each unique combination of these data items. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Market_volumes_UK_only]
10133 Unique Rule Error Each combination of the dimensions (Organisational unit level 1, Organisational unit level 2, Organisational unit level 3 (if applicable), Country of exposure, Profit or loss item level 1 other expense, Profit or loss item level 2 other expense, Projection period, and Scenario) should be uniquely populated in the template i.e. there should not be multiple rows of data for each unique combination of these data items. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Other_expense_details]
10134 Unique Rule Error Each combination of the dimensions (Organisational unit level 1, Organisational unit level 2, Organisational unit level 3 (if applicable), Country of exposure, Profit or loss item level 1 other income, Profit or loss item level 2 other income, Asset liability class retail other income and Other income product type, Projection period, and Scenario) should be uniquely populated in the template i.e. there should not be multiple rows of data for each unique combination of these data items. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Other_income_details]
10135 Unique Rule Error Each combination of the dimensions (Profit or loss item level 1, Profit or loss item level 2, Projection period, and Scenario) should be uniquely populated in the template i.e. there should not be multiple rows of data for each unique combination of these data items. Always [BalanceSheetProjections][Profit_or_loss_group_only]

Exceptions to be raised outside of a tolerance threshold of 1%. BOE Discretion [CapitalAndOtherProjections][Mortgage_arrears_repo_and_sales]
          [RetailMortgageCredit][Arrears]
